abstract: The tentative deal would settle a suit by the Commodity Futures Trading Commission over the collapse of the brokerage firm MF Global.
snippet: The tentative deal would settle a suit by the Commodity Futures Trading Commission over the collapse of the brokerage firm MF Global.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nearly five years after Jon S. Corzine presided over the collapse of the brokerage firm MF Global and became a target of federal investigations, his legal ordeal might be drawing to a close.

abstract: Yes, the Republican nominee wears Brioni — as well as suits by the Brooklyn tailor Martin Greenfield.
snippet: Yes, the Republican nominee wears Brioni — as well as suits by the Brooklyn tailor Martin Greenfield.
lead_paragraph: The press took note when Hillary Clinton wore pantsuits from the American label Ralph Lauren at the Democratic National Convention and at the first presidential debate. But the brands favored by her opponent, Donald J. Trump, have slipped under the radar.

abstract: Our team of reporters fact-checked Hillary Clinton and Donald J. Trump on the economy, trade and other issues.
snippet: Our team of reporters fact-checked Hillary Clinton and Donald J. Trump on the economy, trade and other issues.
lead_paragraph: Hillary Clinton and Donald J. Trump kept fact-checkers busy throughout their first debate on Monday night as they sparred over their policies and records on the economy, national security, the environment and their personal pasts. In keeping with how he has run his campaign, Mr. Trump stretched the facts more often than Mrs. Clinton did; a couple of times, Mrs. Clinton literally called out for fact-checkers from the stage. (Here’s how we analyzed it live, and  the highlights.)

abstract: Twitter has relied on stock-based compensation more than its peers in Silicon Valley, and that has unavoidable implications for potential buyers.
snippet: Twitter has relied on stock-based compensation more than its peers in Silicon Valley, and that has unavoidable implications for potential buyers.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Buying Twitter would be a challenge for a number of reasons. Among the lesser-explored ones: The struggling social network pays out so much stock to its employees.
